Apprehensions for 2019

sg %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  count(year, half, appreh, place, wt = women_18_59+women_60+men_18_64+men_65) %>%
  spread(place, n, fill = 0) %>%
  mutate(appreh = ifelse(appreh == "tak", "yes", "no")) %>%
  select(year, half, `same year` = appreh, `within country`= kraj, `airports` = `lotnicza zewntrzna`,
         `Ukraine` = `Ukraina`, `Russia` = Rosja, `Belarus` = `Biaoru`) %>%
  xtable(caption = "sfsfsa", label = "tab-sg-basic", digits = 0) %>%
  print.xtable(include.rownames = F, caption = "afasf", caption.placement = "top", format.args = list(big.mark = ","))

Police data for 2019

police %>%
  mutate(half = ifelse(quarter %in% 1:2, "I", "II")) %>%
  distinct(sheet, id, pesel, half) %>%
  mutate(pesel = replace_na(pesel, "NIE"), 
         pesel= factor(pesel, c("TAK", "NIE"), c("Yes", "No"), ordered = T)) %>%
  count(year = as.character(2019), half, pesel, type = sheet) %>%
  spread(type, n, fill = 0) %>%
  select(year:pesel, process, searching, traffic, criminal) %>%
  xtable(caption = "sfsfsa", label = "tab-sg-basic", digits = 0) %>%
  print.xtable(include.rownames = F, caption = "afasf", caption.placement = "top", format.args = list(big.mark = ","))

PESEL data for 2019

1 = brak adresu w Polsce 2 = aktualny pobyt czasowy 3 = aktualny pobyt stay 4 = wymeldowny donikd 5 = nieaktualny pobyt czasowy 6 = kraj zamieszkania poza Polsk) Pe: 1-kob, 2-mczy Wiek - podzia na ekonomiczne grupy wieku: 1 = - wiek przedprodukcyjny do 17 lat - wiek produkcyjny: 2 = - dla mczyzn 18-64, 3 = - dla kobiet 18-59, - wiek poprodukcyjny 4 =- dla mczyzn 65 i wicej, 5 = - dla kobiet 60 i wicej.

Stan cywilny 1 = kawaler, panna; 2 = onaty, zamna; 3 = wdowiec, wdowa; 4 = rozwiedziony, rozwiedziona; null = brak danych

Woj Miejsce zameldowania lub ostatniego zameldowania (jeeli jest podane w rejestrze PESEL). Kody w nawiasach null = brak danych DOLNOLSKIE (02) KUJAWSKO-POMORSKIE (04) LUBELSKIE (06) LUBUSKIE (08) DZKIE (10) MAOPOLSKIE (12) MAZOWIECKIE (14) OPOLSKIE (16) PODKARPACKIE (18) PODLASKIE (20) POMORSKIE (22) LSKIE (24) WITOKRZYSKIE (26) WARMISKO-MAZURSKIE (28) WIELKOPOLSKIE (30) ZACHODNIOPOMORSKIE (32)

BYE WARSZAWSKIE (01) BYE BIALSKOPODLASKI (03) BYE BIAOSTOCKIE (05) BYE BIELSKIE (07) BYE BYDGOSKIE (09) BYE CHEMSKIE (11) BYE CIECHANOWSKIE (13) BYE CZSTOCHOWSKIE (15) BYE ELBLSKIE (17) BYE GDASKIE (19) BYE GORZOWSKIE (21) BYE JELENIOGRSKIE (23) BYE KALISKIE (25) BYE KATOWICKIE (27) BYE KIELECKIE (29) BYE KONISKIE (31) BYE KOSZALISKIE (33) BYE KRAKOWSKIE (35) BYE KRONIESKIE (37) BYE LEGNICKIE (39) BYE LESZCZYSKIE (41) BYE LUBELSKIE (43) BYE OMYSKIE (45) BYE DZKIE (47) BYE NOWOSDECKIE (49) BYE OLSZTYSKIE (51) BYE OPOLSKIE (53) BYE OSTROCKIE (55) BYE PILSKIE (57) BYE PIOTRKOWSKIE (59) BYE POCKIE (61) BYE POZNASKIE (63) BYE PRZEMYSKIE (65) BYE RADOMSKIE (67) BYE RZESZOWSKIE (69) BYE SIEDLECKIE (71) BYE SIERADZKIE (73) BYE SKIERNIEWICKIE (75) BYE SUPSKIE (77) BYE SUWALSKIE (79) BYE SZCZECISKIE (81) BYE TARNOBRZESKIE (83) BYE TARNOWSKIE (85) BYE TORUSKIE (87) BYE WABRZYSKIE (89) BYE WOCAWSKIE (91) BYE WROCAWSKIE (93) BYE ZAMOJSKIE (95) BYE ZIELONOGRSKIE (97) NIEZNANE (99)

countries_all %>%
  group_by(country, country_iso3n, half, sex) %>%
  summarise_at(vars(pesel:police_all), sum) %>%
  mutate(country = ifelse(border > 0 & police_all > 0 & police_all / pesel < 1, country, "other")) %>%
  group_by(country, half, sex) %>%
  summarise_at(vars(pesel:police_all), sum) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(log_police_pesel = log(police_all/pesel),
         log_border_pesel = log(border/pesel),
         log_pesel = log(pesel)) -> m

m 
m %>%
#  filter(country != "Ukraine") %>%
ggplot(data = ., 
       aes(x = log_police_pesel, y =log_border_pesel, size = sqrt(pesel))) + 
  geom_point(shape = 1) + geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = F) + facet_wrap(~half) + 
   ggpubr::stat_cor(method = "pearson")


m %>%
 # filter(country != "Ukraine") %>%
ggplot(data = ., 
       aes(x = log_pesel,y = log_border_pesel, size = sqrt(pesel))) + 
  geom_point(shape = 1) + geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = F) + facet_wrap(~half) + 
   ggpubr::stat_cor(method = "pearson")

m  %>%
  group_by(half) %>%
  do(m = broom::tidy(lm(log_border_pesel ~ -1 + log_pesel + log_police_pesel, data = .)),
     inf = broom::glance(lm(log_border_pesel ~ -1 + log_pesel + log_police_pesel, data = .))) %>%
  unnest(inf) %>%
  unnest(m, names_repair = "universal")  %>%
  dplyr::select(half, estimate, std.error, adj.r.squared)
